episodes.title: The Governor's Pleasure
episodes.plot: Bea returns to Wentworth with a heavy charge over the murder of Braydon Holt, while Ferguson makes it clear that she owns Bea. Battle begins over the control of the prison.

episodes.title: Failing Upwards
episodes.plot: Liz makes a tough decision about her and her family. Franky loses someone close to her, while Bea asserts her dominance as top dog. While Fletch continues his rehab after being struck by a van.

episodes.title: Knives Out
episodes.plot: Franky's in trouble with her supply cut and her power base decimated, she's on her own when prisoners come after her to claim what they're owed.

episodes.title: Righteous Acts
episodes.plot: Liz's world is rocked with the arrival of a new prisoner. Franky commences her sessions with Bridget, and admits to a desire for revenge against Bea.

episodes.title: Mercy
episodes.plot: As Fletch readjusts to work life, Bea must forgo closely held morals as she engages in a secret plan to bring down Ferguson. Bea agrees to a visit with Kaz Proctor to demand she and her group stop committing violence in her name.

episodes.title: Evidence
episodes.plot: Ferguson is blindsided by Jodie's complaint to the ombudsman. Channing attempts damage control, but Jodie's accusations of brutality promise to be very damaging for the Governor.

episodes.title: The Long Game
episodes.plot: Bea is held in the psych unit and struggles to accept she had a psychotic episode. Franky is pushed to reveal her biggest secret.

episodes.title: Goldfish
episodes.plot: When Bea encourages Doreen to uncover the truth behind Ferguson's obsession with "Jianna", Ferguson's renewed interest in Doreen brings on labour.

episodes.title: Freak Show
episodes.plot: Bea's war with Ferguson comes to a head after Doreen returns from the hospital and tensions between Bea and those closest to her reach boiling point, as Vera finally learns the truth behind Jodie's injury after Bridget is forced to resign.

episodes.title: A Higher Court
episodes.plot: Franky's parole hearing is brought forward but it's not all smooth sailing as Franky deals with a jealous Kim. As Will finally learns the truth about who killed his wife and Ferguson's plan to set up several inmates falters.

episodes.title: The Living and the Dead
episodes.plot: When Bea uses her alliance with Fletch to drive a wedge between Vera and Ferguson, her actions set in motion an unstoppable chain of events.

episodes.title: Blood and Fire
episodes.plot: The walls are closing in on Ferguson - who will survive the final showdown?
